race.comment: ALABAMA FOX (3) warmed up when the race was all over first-up at the Kensington track. An extra 150m today is to her advantage as she scored second-up last prep over this trip. Suited by the small field and looks hard to beat, the lone runner not from the Waller stable. The unbeaten FROSTY GIRL (1) is back from a four-month spell. Came from well back in the field in both her wins, each time at 1300m. This looks a nice race to launch the second campaign. PICTOR (6) showed great determination to salute at the Kensington track last time. Coming along nicely and is more than capable of a repeat performance. PHILATELIC (7) resumes and had transferred to the premier yard over the break. Trialling well and showed enough last prep to suggest he has the ability to be competitive here.
